Work from-home advice and lockdowns during the pandemic hit the takeaway giant hard. But it said it returned to profitability in March. This week Pret launched a new affordable menu range to help people who are feeling the pinch with the cost-of-living crisis. Accounts just filed at Companies House showed it made an operating loss of £225.9million in 2021, down from £343million in 2020. Sales for the first half of 2022 reached £357.8million, up 230 percent on last year.